cancer%20is%20now%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolon-cancer-leading-cause-cancer-death-under-50-shocking-experts-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eleading%20cause%20of%20cancer%20death%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20people%20under%2050.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECancer%20can%20be%20caused%20by%20a%20variety%20of%20factors%2C%20including%20family%20history%2C%20genetic%20mutations%2C%20and%20environmental%20pollutants%20%E2%80%94%20all%20things%20out%20of%20our%20control%20%E2%80%94%20but%20some%20risk%20can%20be%20mitigated%20with%20lifestyle%20modifications.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2298706e6a-6bdc-46e9-b233-3aead3a08e3c%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EFollow%20a%20diverse%2C%20Mediterranean-ish%20diet%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224468%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Salad%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F698277a6e1ba468a96ab56d0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223351%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EEating%20whole%2C%20fiber-rich%20foods%20can%20lower%20cancer%20risk.%3Cp%3EOrganic%20Media%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EResearch%20shows%20that%20diets%20involving%20lots%20of%20ultra-processed%20foods%20(UPFs)%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feating-ultra-processed-foods-ovarian-brain-cancer-risk-2022-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elinked%20to%20higher%20cancer%20risk%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They%20can%20increase%20inflammation%20and%20disrupt%20the%20gut%20microbiome%2C%20increasing%20the%20risk%20of%20colon%20and%20ovarian%20cancer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20diet%20rich%20in%20whole%20foods%20is%20the%20best%20way%20to%20go.%20Dr.%20Daniel%20Landau%2C%20an%20oncologist%20specializing%20in%20genitourinary%20cancers%2C%20previously%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20he%20mostly%20follows%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmediterranean-diet-best-healthy-eating-longevity-rankings-2025-1%5C%