%3E%3Cstrong%3EVizio%20OS%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Vizio%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EGoogle%20TV%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Sony%2C%20TCL%2C%20Hisense%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ERoku%20TV%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Roku%2C%20TCL%2C%20Hisense%2C%20Onn%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EFire%20TV%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Amazon%2C%20Panasonic%2C%20Toshiba%2C%20Insignia%2C%20Pioneer%2C%20Hisense%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20a%20few%20services%20may%20be%20missing%20here%20and%20there%2C%20all%20major%20streaming%20apps%20are%20supported%20across%20every%20operating%20system.%20However%2C%20each%20system's%20navigation%20style%2C%20personalization%20options%2C%20and%20extra%20features%20differ.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20prefer%20Roku's%20interface%20because%20it%20is%20the%20simplest%2C%20most%20user-friendly%2C%20and%20most%20reliable.%20However%2C%20its%20visual%20style%20is%20a%20bit%20outdated%20compared%20to%20other%20options%20that%20present%20a%20more%20content-focused%20approach.%20Ultimately%2C%20every%20system%20has%20pros%20and%20cons%2C%20but%20they%20all%20get%20the%20job%20done.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20unhappy%20with%20your%20TV's%20built-in%20interface%2C%20you%20can%20purchase%20a%20separate%20streaming%20device%20with%20your%20preferred%20platform.%20Roku%20and%20Fire%20TV%20options%20are%20often%20sold%20for%20as%20low%20as%20%2420.%20Check%20out%20our%20guides%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fbest-streaming-devices%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebest%20streaming%20devices%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Famazon-fire-tv-buying-guide%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebest%20Fire%20TVs%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20more%20details.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EWhat's%20the%20difference%20between%20OLED%20and%20QLED%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EOLED%20and%20QLED%20TVs%20are%20two%20of%20the%20most%20popular%20display%20types%20on%20the%20market%2C%20each%20with%20its%20own%20pros%20and%20cons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOLED%20TVs%20have%20self-illuminating%20screens.%20This%20means%20they%20can%20dim%20and%20brighten%20each%20pixel%20to%20create%20an%20infinite%20contrast%20ratio.%20This%20makes%20OLED%20the%20ideal%20choice%20for%20individuals%20who%20seek%20the%20ultimate%20image%20quality%2C%20particularly%20if%20you%20enjoy%20watching%20movies%20in%20a%20dark%20home%20theater.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EQLED%20TVs%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20are%20a%20type%20of%20LED%20TV%20that%20uses%20older%20LCD%20panel%20technology%20and%20requires%20a%20backlight%20to%20illuminate%20its%20pixels.%20These%20backlights%20can%20include%20multiple%20zones%20to%20brighten%20and%20dim%20specific%20areas%2C%20but%20even%20the%20most%20advanced%20QLED%20models%20can't%20match%20OLEDs'%20pixel-level%20contrast.%20This%20can%20cause%20an%20uneven%20look%20in%20dark%20scenes%2C%20where%20halos%20appear%20around%20bright%20objects%20or%20black%20levels%20appear%20washed%20out%2C%20looking%20gray.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhere%20QLED%20TVs%20have%20an%20edge%2C%20however%2C%20is%20with%20max%20brightness.%20Midrange%20and%20high-end%20QLED%20TVs%20can%20get%20brighter%20than%20most%20OLEDs.%20QLED%20models%20are%20also%20generally%20less%20expensive%20than%20OLED%20TVs%20and%20pose%20no%20risk%20of%20burn-in.%20For%20more%20details%20on%20the%20differences%20between%20each%20panel%20type%2C%20check%20out%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fqled-vs-oled%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EQLED%20vs.%20OLED%3C%2Fa%3E%20comparison.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EAre%208K%20TVs%20worth%20it%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20benefits%20of%208K%20over%204K%20are%20extremely%20subtle%20and%20hard%20to%20notice%20unless%20you%20sit%20close%20to%20a%20very%20large%20TV%20(75%20inches%20or%20more).%20It's%20also%20important%20to%20remember%20that%208K%20content%20is%20rare%2C%20as%20virtually%20all%20movies%20and%20TV%20shows%20are%20still%20produced%20in%204K%20or%20even%20lower%20resolutions.%20Although%208K%20TVs%20can%20upscale%204K%20content%20to%20produce%20a%20slightly%20sharper%20image%2C%20the%20picture%20quality%20upgrade%20is%20too%20small%20to%20justify%20the%20premium%20that%208K%20TVs%20cost.%20As%20it%20stands%2C%20we%20recommend%204K%20TVs%20over%20pricier%208K%20models.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EWhat%20is%20burn-in%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fbest-oled-tvs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebest%20OLED%20TVs%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20technically%20susceptible%20to%20a%20phenomenon%20known%20as%20burn-in.%20If%20a%20static%20image%20%E2%80%94%20the%20CNN%20or%20ESPN%20logo%20in%20the%20corner%2C%20for%20example%20%E2%80%94%20is%20left%20on%20the%20screen%20for%20hours%20on%20end%2C%20a%20faint%2C%20ghostly%20image%20can%20become%20stuck%20on%20the%20TV.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20OLED%20owners%20should%20be%20aware%20of%20this%20risk%2C%20OLED%20TVs%20have%20built-in%20measures%20to%20prevent%20burn-in%2C%20including%20pixel%20refreshers%20and%20pixel%20shift%20modes.%20Publications%20like%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rtings.com%2Ftv%2Ftests%2Flongevity-burn-in-test-updates-and-results%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERtings%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20conducted%20long-term%20tests%20with%20OLEDs%2C%20and%20while%20their%20results%20indicate%20that%20burn-in%20is%20possible%2C%20the%20tests%20suggest%20that%20individuals%20with%20regular%20viewing%20habits%20don't%20need%20to%20worry%20about%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20owned%20an%20LG%20CX%20OLED%20TV%20for%20over%20three%20years%2C%20and%20the%20display%20has%20no%20signs%20of%20burn-in.%20Though%20burn-in%20is%20something%20that%20QLED%20TV%20owners%20don't%20have%20to%20think%20twice%20about%2C%20in%20my%20experience%2C%20as%20long%20as%20you%20don't%20plan%20on%20watching%20CNN%20all%20day%2C%20burn-in%20shouldn't%20be%20a%20factor%20when%20deciding%20whether%20to%20buy%20an%20OLED.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EWhat%20is%20HDMI%202.1%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EMany%204K%20TVs%20in%20the%20mid-%20and%20premium%20tiers%20now%20include%20one%20or%20more%20HDMI%202.1%20inputs.%20HDMI%202.1%20supports%204K%20at%20120Hz%20(some%20brands%20even%20support%20144Hz%20with%20a%20PC)%2C%20along%20with%20features%20such%20as%20variable%20refresh%20rate%20(VRR)%20and%20auto%20low%20latency%20mode%20(ALLM)%2C%20to%20deliver%20smooth%20gaming%20with%20reduced%20lag.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEvery%20device%20in%20your%20home%20entertainment%20chain%20needs%20to%20be%20compatible%20with%20the%20HDMI%202.1%20specification%20to%20enable%20its%20features.%20Therefore%2C%20if%20you%20have%20a%20gaming%20console%20connected%20to%20a%20soundbar%20that's%20connected%20to%20your%20TV%2C%20all%20three%20components%20must%20support%20HDMI%202.1.%20Likewise%2C%20you%20need%20to%20use%20ultra-high-speed%20HDMI%20cables%20rated%20for%2048Gbps%20to%20support%20the%20bandwidth%20required%20for%20an%20HDMI%202.1%20signal.%20Visit%20our%20guide%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fbest-hdmi-cables%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebest%20HDMI%20cables%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20affordable%20recommendations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fbest-4k-tvs%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1770157722000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F698257bda645d1188188992f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fbest-4k-tvs%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20best%204K%20TVs%20include%20QLED%20and%20OLED%20models%20from%20Samsung%2C%20LG%2C%20TCL%2C%20and%20Roku.%20Our%20top%20picks%20are%20available%20in%20sizes%20ranging%20from%2042%20to%20115%20inches.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22scohen%40insider.com%20(Steven%20Cohen)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%